#-          Millitary Codes§0
§0
§0PTS = Permission To§0
§0Speak§0
§0
§0On me! = Get in line behind leader who ordered you.§0
§0
§0On my right! = Get on the right of the leader who is commanding you.
#- On my left! = Line on the left of the leader.§0
§0
§0STS! = Shoulder to shoulder next to your fellow soldiers in front of the leader.§0
§0
§0(You may not speak during training without Your PTS granted.)§0
§0
§0       Next page
#-       Archer codes§0
§0      ------------§0
§0
§0Range arms! = Pull out your bow§0
§0  §0
§0Order arms! = Do not hold your bow if you were holding it§0
§0
§0Make ready! = Pull your Bow string straight back do not fire. Next page
#- Aim! = Find your target before the leader orders you to fire. Aim is only used when bow is fully loaded and string is pulled back.§0
§0
§0Blanket fire, 3 sheets! = Fire your bow 3 times, make sure there is 3 seconds between each shot. 
#- Ripple fire from the left! = Soldier to the left of the line fires his bow, then the person next to him fires, and it goes on till it reaches the end of the line.§0
§0
§0Ripple fire from the right! = Same concept as Left ripple, but from the right.
#- Central ripple! =§0
§0Ripple starts from the man in the middle. then the fire goes from the right and the left until the line reaches the two last men at the sides of the line.§0
§0
§0Volley fire! = Every archer fires at the same time, just one shot. Next
#-  Fire at will! = Fire repeatedly at the enemy until the leader says "Cease fire!"§0
§0
§0"Cease him!" = Attack The man the leader told you to cease, if he does not surrender, kill him.§0
§0
§0Next
#- Charge arms! = If you are an archer, your setup will still have a melee weapon, just weaker than that of§0
§0infatries. Pull out your melee weapon, ando do not charge until the leader orders: "Charge!"§0
§0
§0Fall back! = Run from the battle/enemy.
#- If there is no leader, you are to battle doing things yourself, there is no different types of formations or types of fire without a leader. §0
§0
§0
§0Any orders forgotten to be written or that are too complex to explain is in training.
#- 